@startuml level-3c-components-state-machine
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
HIDE_STEREOTYPE()

title JOTP Level 3: State Machine Components

Container_Boundary(stm, "State Machine Engine") {

  Component(statemachine, "StateMachine<S,E,D>", "Engine", "gen_statem full parity\nSealed event/action/transition\nEngine event loop\nTimeout management")

  Component(smevent, "SMEvent<E>", "Event Sealed Type", "User(E): application event\nStateTimeout: per-state timer\nEventTimeout: event timer\nGenericTimeout: arbitrary timer\nInternal: synthetic\nEnter: state entry")

  Component(action, "Action", "Action Sealed Type", "Postpone: defer event\nNextEvent(E): queue event\nSetStateTimeout/CancelStateTimeout\nSetEventTimeout/CancelEventTimeout\nSetGenericTimeout/CancelGenericTimeout\nReply(pid, msg): reply to caller")

  Component(transition, "Transition", "Transition Sealed", "NextState(S): move to S\nKeepState(): stay in S\nRepeatState(): loop handler\nStop(reason): terminate\nStopAndReply(pid, msg): reply + stop\nAll include actions()")

  Component(transitionfn, "TransitionFn<S,E,D>", "Handler Interface", "apply(S, SMEvent<E>, D) -> Transition\nPure function: state + event + data\nReturns transition + actions\nCan modify data")

  Component(builder, "StateMachineBuilder", "Fluent Builder", "withStateEnter() callbacks\nBuilder<S,E,D> sealed type\nDefine all states before build\nOptional Enter event")

  Component(eventmanager, "EventManager<E>", "Event Dispatcher", "Typed event hub\naddHandler(id, handler)\nnotify(event) async dispatch\nsyncNotify(event) blocking\nHandler isolation: crash ≠ kill manager")

  Component(parallel, "Parallel", "Structured Fan-Out", "StructuredTaskScope wrapper\nFail-fast: cancel on first error\nWait semantics\nVirtual thread per task")

  Rel(statemachine, smevent, "receives")
  Rel(statemachine, action, "produces actions")
  Rel(statemachine, transition, "applies")
  Rel(statemachine, transitionfn, "invokes handler")
  Rel(builder, statemachine, "builds")
  Rel(eventmanager, transitionfn, "dispatches to")
  Rel(parallel, transitionfn, "fan-out parallel")

  note right of statemachine
    **StateMachine<S,E,D>** — OTP gen_statem:
    Full parity with Erlang gen_statem.
    Engine manages sealed event/action/transition hierarchy.
    Timeout management: StateTimeout, EventTimeout, GenericTimeout.
    Priorities: User > Enter > Internal > Postponed.
  end note

  note right of smevent
    **SMEvent<E>** — Sealed event hierarchy:
    User(E): application event.
    StateTimeout: per-state timer fired.
    EventTimeout: specific event timer.
    GenericTimeout: arbitrary named timer.
    Internal: synthetic internal transition.
    Enter: state entry notification.
  end note

  note right of action
    **Action** — Sealed result actions:
    Postpone: defer event to next state.
    NextEvent(E): insert into priority queue.
    SetStateTimeout/CancelStateTimeout.
    SetEventTimeout/CancelEventTimeout.
    SetGenericTimeout/CancelGenericTimeout.
    Reply(pid, msg): reply to caller (gen_server call).
  end note

  note right of transition
    **Transition** — Sealed state transitions:
    NextState(S, actions): move to state S.
    KeepState(actions): remain in current state.
    RepeatState(actions): re-invoke handler.
    Stop(reason): terminate state machine.
    StopAndReply(pid, msg, reason): reply + terminate.
    All variants include actions() list.
  end note

  note right of transitionfn
    **TransitionFn<S,E,D>** — Handler interface:
    apply(S state, SMEvent<E> event, D data).
    Pure function: no side effects allowed.
    Returns Transition (sealed).
    Can mutate data (passed by reference).
  end note

  note right of builder
    **StateMachineBuilder** — Fluent builder:
    withStateEnter() adds Enter event callbacks.
    Builder<S,E,D> sealed type.
    Define all states before build().
    Optional initial state Enter.
  end note

  note right of eventmanager
    **EventManager<E>** — Event dispatcher:
    Typed event hub: addHandler(id, handler).
    notify(event): async dispatch to all.
    syncNotify(event): blocking dispatch.
    Handler isolation: crash ≠ kill manager.
  end note

  note right of parallel
    **Parallel** — Structured fan-out:
    StructuredTaskScope wrapper (Java 21+).
    Fail-fast: cancel on first error.
    One virtual thread per task.
    Scope auto-closes (cleanup).
  end note

  note on link : Engine loop: dequeue SMEvent -> handler(state, event, data) -> Transition<actions> -> apply actions -> new state
  note on link : InsertedEvents priority queue (User > Internal > Postponed)
  note on link : StateTimeout auto-cancel on state change; EventTimeout auto-cancel on any event
  note on link : Postpone/replay across state transitions; stale timeouts discarded
}

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml